#. Tag: title
#: workflows.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid "Workflows with &kphotoalbum;"
msgstr "Poteki dela z &kphotoalbum;om"

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Workflow is rather important aspect in digital imaging. In this chapter we "
"describe different workflows that fit on different needs. There are many "
"different factors that must be considered when developing a workflow. "
"Hopefully these examples will provide you with sufficient ideas of how to "
"tune-up your own method of working with digital imaging."
msgstr ""
"Potek dela je precej pomemben vidik pri digitalni obdelavi slik. V tem "
"poglavju opisujemo različne poteke dela, ki ustrezajo različnim potrebam. "
"Pri razvoju poteka dela je treba upoštevati veliko različnih dejavnikov. "
"Upajmo, da vam bodo ti primeri dali dovolj idej o tem, kako prilagoditi "
"svojo metodo dela z digitalnimi slikami."

#. Tag: title
#: workflows.docbook:19
#, no-c-format
msgid "RAW workflow using &kphotoalbum; and Bibble5/AfterShot Pro"
msgstr "Potek dela RAW z &kphotoalbum; in Bibble5/AfterShot Pro"

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When shooting RAW images the files from camera must be developed to commonly "
"recognized format like JPEG or TIFF. There are a few options to choose from "
"when working on Linux. For example RawTherapee and Ufraw are open-source "
"alternatives when Bibble5/AfterShot Pro are commercial application for this "
"purpose."
msgstr ""
"Pri snemanju slik RAW je treba datoteke iz fotoaparata razviti v splošno "
"priznan format, kot sta JPEG ali TIFF. Pri delu v Linuxu lahko izbirate med "
"nekaj možnostmi. Na primer, RawTherapee in Ufraw sta odprtokodni "
"alternativi, medtem ko sta Bibble5/AfterShot Pro komercialni aplikaciji za "
"ta namen."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:26
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A few settings are recommended for a RAW workflow. First is to enable the "
"using of the embedded thumbnail. This will give a tremendous speed boost "
"over decoding each raw file each time they are viewed (check also the "
"minimum dimension configuration to ensure decent quality). Second one is for "
"the New Image Finder to automatically stack the developed versions over the "
"RAW file (developed image must be on same directory as the original). This "
"requires regular expressions as described in <xref linkend=\"opt-search-new"
"\"/>. Two helper scripts are provided in &kphotoalbum; sources to help in "
"RAW workflow. These are open-raw.desktop and open-raw.pl. The first one "
"enables GUI applications to open the RAW files in the open-raw.pl script "
"that tries to find the original RAW file and open that instead of the "
"developed image."
msgstr ""
"Za potek dela RAW je priporočenih nekaj nastavitev. Najprej omogočite "
"uporabo vdelane sličice. To bo izjemno povečalo hitrost pri dekodiranju "
"vsake neobdelane datoteke ob vsakem ogledu (preverite tudi konfiguracijo "
"najmanjše dimenzije, da zagotovite primerno kakovost). Drugi je, da iskalnik "
"novih slik samodejno zloži razvite različice v datoteko RAW (razvita slika "
"mora biti v istem imeniku kot izvirnik). To zahteva regularne izraze, kot je "
"opisano v <xref linkend=\"opt-search-new\"/>. Dva pomožna skripta sta na "
"voljo v &kphotoalbum; vire za pomoč pri poteku dela RAW. To sta open-raw."
"desktop in open-raw.pl. Prvi omogoča aplikacijam GUI odpiranje datotek RAW v "
"skriptu open-raw.pl, ki poskuša najti izvirno datoteko RAW in jo odpreti "
"namesto razvite slike."

#. Tag: title
#: workflows.docbook:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sending Images to RAW Editor"
msgstr "Pošiljanje slik v urejevalnik RAW"

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First step in actual workflow is to copy the images from camera to the "
"computer. A simple copy on a terminal window is all that is needed:"
msgstr ""
"Prvi korak v dejanskem delovnem procesu je kopiranje slik iz fotoaparata v "
"računalnik. Enostavna kopija v terminalskem oknu je vse, kar potrebujete:"

#. Tag: screen
#: workflows.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput><command>cp</command> <option>-a</option> <filename>/"
"media/.../101CANON/</filename> <filename>~/Pictures/2012/sample</filename>\n"
"  </userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput><command>cp</command> <option>-a</option> <filename>/"
"media/.../101CANON/</filename> <filename>~/Pictures/2012/sample</filename> </"
"userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:53
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then either start &kphotoalbum; or run <menuchoice><guimenu>Maintenance</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Rescan for Images and Videos</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>. New images should be found and now is time for initially "
"tagging the images. As I usually photograph while traveling I first insert "
"the place. Select <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> and browse to the new "
"directory. Then go to the <guilabel>Show Thumbnails</guilabel>, select all "
"and <guimenu>Annotate Multiple Items at a Time</guimenu> or <keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>2</keycap></keycombo>. Insert the proper place like "
"Finland-Helsinki (see <xref linkend=\"sec-member-groups-in-property-editor\"/"
">)."
msgstr ""
"Nato zaženite &kphotoalbum; ali zaženite <menuchoice><guimenu>Vzdrževanje</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovno skeniranje slik in videoposnetkov</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Najti je treba nove slike in zdaj je čas za prvo "
"označevanje slik. Kot običajno fotografiram med potovanjem, najprej vstavim "
"kraj. Izberite <guilabel>Mapa</guilabel> in poiščite nov imenik. Nato "
"pojdite na <guilabel>Pokaži sličice</guilabel>, izberite vse in "
"<guimenu>Dodajte opombe več elementom hkrati</guimenu> ali <keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>2</keycap></keycombo>. Vstavite ustrezno mesto, kot "
"je Finska-Helsinki (glejte <xref linkend=\"sec-member-groups-in-property-"
"editor\"/>)."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now that the new images are easy to find I do the initial ranking and "
"deletion. For this I go to the thumbnail view and start the Viewer by "
"hitting &Enter;. I use rating for good images, just press the appropriate "
"number from <keycap>1</keycap> to <keycap>5</keycap>. I only give 3 to 5 "
"ratings and hit <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Del</keycap></"
"keycombo> for the bad photos to delete them. At this point I might add also "
"People names if there happens to be a diver in the photo. Once the first "
"round is done I exit the Viewer by hitting &Esc; and select "
"<guimenuitem>Delete file from disk</guimenuitem> to get rid off the bad "
"images for good."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj, ko je nove slike enostavno najti, naredim začetno razvrščanje in "
"brisanje. Za to grem v pogled sličic in zaženem pregledovalnik s pritiskom "
"na &Enter;. Za dobre slike uporabljam oceno, samo pritisnite ustrezno "
"številko od <keycap>1</keycap> do <keycap>5</keycap>. Dam samo ocene od 3 do "
"5 in pritisnem <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Del</keycap></"
"keycombo> za slabe fotografije, da jih izbrišem. Na tej točki lahko dodam "
"tudi imena ljudi, če je na fotografiji potapljač. Ko je prvi krog končan, "
"zapustim pregledovalnik tako, da pritisnem &Esc; in izberem "
"<guimenuitem>Izbriši datoteko z diska</guimenuitem>, da se za vedno znebim "
"slabih slik."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next I select only the images that have high enough rating using the search "
"function. Naturally the Place has to be set if search is started with "
"<keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>F</keycap></keycombo>. However, if "
"search is invoked from the Main Window the current selection is drilled down "
"to the more precise match. Anyway, at this point I go through the better "
"rated images again doing refining on the rating. E.g. if I have 5 similar "
"photos of one Nudibranch species I generally decrease the rating of the "
"poorer images and might increase the best one. Comparing images can be done "
"by selecting the ones you want to compare and starting the Viewer. Removing "
"images from the Viewer selection can be done with <keycap>Delete</keycap>. "
"This only disables the viewing of the current image while within the Viewer, "
"nothing is removed or deleted. This allows comparing 2 or 3 better images "
"next to each other moving between them with <keycap>PgUp</keycap> and "
"<keycap>PgDn</keycap>. I quite commonly use a <literal>tmp</literal> "
"category to mark &eg; crabs and shrimps to be easily able to display only "
"selected type of images during the later phases of selection and "
"identification."
msgstr ""
"Nato s funkcijo iskanja izberem samo slike, ki imajo dovolj visoko oceno. "
"Seveda mora biti mesto nastavljeno, če se iskanje začne s <keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>F</keycap></keycombo>. Če pa se iskanje prikliče iz "
"glavnega okna, se trenutni izbor poglobi do natančnejšega ujemanja. Kakor "
"koli že, na tej točki ponovno pregledam bolje ocenjene slike in izboljšam "
"oceno. Npr. če imam 5 podobnih fotografij ene vrste Nodibranch, običajno "
"znižam oceno slabših slik in morda povečam najboljšo. Slike lahko primerjate "
"tako, da izberete tiste, ki jih želite primerjati, in zaženete "
"pregledovalnik. Odstranjevanje slik iz izbire pregledovalnika lahko izvedete "
"s <keycap>Izbriši</keycap>. To onemogoči samo ogled trenutne slike, medtem "
"ko se v pregledovalniku nič ne odstrani ali izbriše. To omogoča primerjavo 2 "
"ali 3 boljših slik eno poleg druge, ki se premikajo med njimi s "
"<keycap>PgUp</keycap> in <keycap>PgDn</keycap>. Precej pogosto uporabljam "
"kategorijo <literal>tmp</literal> za označevanje &eg;. rakov in kozic, da bi "
"v kasnejših fazah izbire in identifikacije enostavno prikazali samo izbrano "
"vrsto slik."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After a reduced amount of images is left I start tagging them. I add the "
"Latin Name of the species and Common Name. Whenever I have these two "
"categories completed I consider the image Done and get rid of the Untagged "
"marking. Note that if you still need to do tagging after developing the RAW "
"image (and auto-stacking them) you need to select the top of collapsed stack "
"(or all images on expanded stack) and select <emphasis>Annotate Multiple "
"Items at a Time</emphasis> to get the whole stack annotated instead of only "
"the topmost image."
msgstr ""
"Ko ostane manjša količina slik, jih začnem označevati. Dodam latinsko ime "
"vrste in splošno ime. Kadarkoli izpolnim ti dve kategoriji, menim, da je "
"slika dokončana in se znebim oznake Neoznačeno. Upoštevajte, da če morate po "
"razvijanju slike RAW (in njihovem samodejnem zlaganju) še vedno označevati, "
"morate izbrati vrh strnjenega sklada (ali vse slike v razširjenem skladu) in "
"izbrati <emphasis>Označi več elementov hkrati</emphasis>, da dobite opombe "
"celotnega sklada namesto le najvišje slike."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The best images are sent to external application for developing. With wanted "
"images selected, right click on selected thumbnail and select "
"<menuchoice><guimenuitem>Invoke External Program</"
"guimenuitem><guimenuitem>All Selected Images</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Send "
"Bibble5</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. The application selected is actually my "
"script that detects if there is a RAW file for the possibly already "
"developed images available and uses that if possible. Within the external "
"application I do some tuning up and cropping if required and then output the "
"developed JPEGs next to the original RAW file. File naming is rather simple, "
"change the extension or add underscore and running number if needed."
msgstr ""
"Najboljše slike se pošljejo zunanji aplikaciji v razvijanje. Z izbranimi "
"želenimi slikami z desno miškino tipko kliknite izbrano sličico in izberite "
"<menuchoice><guimenuitem>Prikliči zunanji program</"
"guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Vse izbrane slike</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Pošlji "
"Bibble5</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Izbrana aplikacija je pravzaprav moj "
"skript, ki zazna, ali je na voljo datoteka RAW za morebiti že razvite slike, "
"in jo uporabi, če je to mogoče. Znotraj zunanje aplikacije naredim nekaj "
"prilagoditev in obrezovanja, če je potrebno, nato pa izpišem razvite JPEG "
"poleg izvirne datoteke RAW. Poimenovanje datoteke je precej preprosto, po "
"potrebi spremenite končnico ali dodajte podčrtaj in tekočo številko."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now that there is plenty of new JPEGs in the image directories I let "
"&kphotoalbum; search for new images and automatically stack the new ones on "
"top of the original RAW (<xref linkend=\"fig-options-file-versions\"/>). "
"Then a final round of selection with the developed images and adding some "
"descriptions if needed."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj, ko je v imenikih slik veliko novih datotek JPEG, sem pustil "
"&kphotoalbum; da poišče nove slike in samodejno zloži nove na prvotni RAW "
"(<xref linkend=\"fig-options-file-versions\"/>). Nato zadnji krog izbire z "
"razvitimi slikami in dodajanjem nekaj opisov, če je potrebno."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Final step is to generate static &HTML; pages and upload to my web server "
"for the enjoyment of friends and colleagues. This I do with the stacks "
"collapsed to only get the developed images to the web page. &HTML; "
"generation is described in <xref linkend=\"chp-generating-html\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Zadnji korak je ustvarjanje statične &HTML; strani in prenos na moj spletni "
"strežnik za uživanje prijateljev in sodelavcev. To naredim s strnjenimi "
"skladi, da na spletno stran prenesem samo razvite slike. &HTML; generiranje "
"je opisano v <xref linkend=\"chp-generating-html\"/>."

#. Tag: title
#: workflows.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Panorama workflow"
msgstr "Potek dela za panoramo"

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Panoramas require a bit different workflow than normal photo editing. This "
"is due to the requirement for multiple source files. The tool of choice for "
"panoramas is Autopano Pro but latest version of &digikam; should do well and "
"fits zero budget. Following list describes the steps required:"
msgstr ""
"Panorame zahtevajo nekoliko drugačen potek dela kot običajno urejanje "
"fotografij. To je posledica zahteve po več izvornih datotekah. Izbrano "
"orodje za panorame je Autopano Pro, vendar najnovejša različica &digikam; "
"mora delovati tudi dobro in ustreza ničelnemu proračunu. Naslednji seznam "
"opisuje potrebne korake:"

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tag the photos belonging to a panorama in &kphotoalbum; appropriately. This "
"is done mainly to avoid discarding images by accident, when sorting out the "
"garbage among the photos taken. You probably want also to stack the set of "
"source images at this point."
msgstr ""
"Označite fotografije, ki pripadajo panorami v &kphotoalbum; ustrezno. To je "
"storjeno predvsem zato, da bi se izognili slučajnemu zavrženju slik pri "
"razvrščanju smeti med posnetimi fotografijami. Verjetno boste na tej točki "
"želeli zložiti tudi niz izvornih slik."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "You have at least two simple options for next step:"
msgstr "Za naslednji korak imate vsaj dve preprosti možnosti:"

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can let Autopano Pro find the panoramas automatically from the photo "
"directory."
msgstr ""
"Programu Autopano Pro lahko dovolite, da samodejno poišče panorame iz "
"imenika fotografij."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Or send the proper images to Autopano Pro on command line to speed things "
"up. This is handy if the image directory contains a lot of images, "
"especially RAW ones. This requires one to fix the script that starts "
"Autopano Pro to accept input and to create a desktop file or invoking "
"external program with own command line."
msgstr ""
"Ali pa pošljite ustrezne slike v Autopano Pro v ukazni vrstici, da pospešite "
"stvari. To je priročno, če imenik slik vsebuje veliko slik, zlasti RAW. Za "
"to je treba popraviti skript, ki zažene Autopano Pro, da sprejme vnos in "
"ustvari namizno datoteko ali prikliče zunanji program z lastno ukazno "
"vrstico."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If it happens that the resulting panorama is missing a small part, you can "
"try to craft it e.g. with the Gimp. Gimp works usually quite well if there "
"is enough \"structure\" to be cloned but there is absolutely no guarantee "
"you will get usable results."
msgstr ""
"Če se zgodi, da nastali panorami manjka majhen del, jo lahko poskusite "
"izdelati npr. z Gimpom. Gimp običajno deluje precej dobro, če je dovolj "
"\"strukture\", ki jo je treba klonirati, vendar ni nobenega zagotovila, da "
"boste dobili uporabne rezultate."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save the new image somewhere under &kphotoalbum;'s image directory and run "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Maintenance</guimenu><guimenuitem>Rescan for Images and "
"Videos</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. This should notice the new panorama and "
"include it in the picture gallery."
msgstr ""
"Shranite novo sliko nekam v imenik slik &kphotoalbum; in zaženite "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Vzdrževanje</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovno skeniranje "
"slik in videoposnetkov</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. To bi moralo opaziti novo "
"panoramo in jo vključiti v galerijo slik."

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have set the AutoStacking of new images properly and name of the new "
"panorama matches the rules for this, the panorama should be on top of the "
"stack. Otherwise sort the images by date, so the new panorama ends up at by "
"the source images and stack them manually. (Autopano Pro seems to write the "
"EXIF info of the first image into the panorama.)"
msgstr ""
"Če ste pravilno nastavili samodejno zlaganje novih slik in se ime nove "
"panorame ujema s pravili za to, mora biti panorama na vrhu sklada. V "
"nasprotnem primeru razvrstite slike po datumu, tako da se nova panorama "
"konča pri izvornih slikah in jih zložite ročno. (Zdi se, da Autopano Pro "
"zapiše podatke EXIF prve slike v panoramo.)"

#. Tag: para
#: workflows.docbook:182
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can still add tagging at this point to the panorama or you might include "
"all the source images also with <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>2</keycap></"
"keycombo>."
msgstr ""
"Na tej točki lahko panorami še vedno dodate oznake ali pa vključite vse "
"izvorne slike tudi s <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>2</keycap></keycombo>."
